<item>
            <title>[CXF-6377] Wrong media type of response</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-6377</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Resource class&lt;br/&gt;
public Response getMediaType() &lt;/p&gt;
{
		MediaType media = MediaType.APPLICATION_ATOM_XML_TYPE;
		Response response = Response.ok().type(media).build();
		return response;
	}

&lt;p&gt;get media type from response on client side is  null.&lt;br/&gt;
Spec 3.8 Determining the MediaType of Responses&lt;br/&gt;
1. If the method returns an instance of Response whose metadata includes the response media type&lt;br/&gt;
(Mspecified) then set Mselected = Mspecified, finish.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
