                            <comment id="14519301" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Wed, 29 Apr 2015 12:54:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Neal,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think this test is invalid. It does not make sense to return a media type if a response entity is absent. &lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;m afraid it needs to be challenged, sorry about it &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sergey&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14519322" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Wed, 29 Apr 2015 13:07:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please watch a &quot;Section 3.7.8 should be clarified&quot; thread on the 370 list&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14520832" author="nbqyqx@163.com" created="Thu, 30 Apr 2015 04:18:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi you mean section 3.8 or 3.7.8? on 3.8 it says if media type specified by response set it and finish.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14521150" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Thu, 30 Apr 2015 08:51:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem with some  of TCK tests is that they basically mechanically test some of spec sentences and by doing so they enforce the runtime to do the bad HTTP, i.e, send a Content-Type which is supposed to describe the body content which is not there at all. So on the wire you&apos;d see:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Content-Type: foo/bar&lt;br/&gt;
Content-Length: 0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;no content here&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is a bad practice. The fact that it is enforced via TCK makes me unhappy at all&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14521245" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Thu, 30 Apr 2015 10:05:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Having said all of the above I&apos;ve decided to get it done by default but also let people optionally block sending Content-Type with empty bodies by setting a property.&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
